MELBOURNE, April 8 -

Western Mining Corp Holdings Ltd &lt;WMNG.S&gt; (WMC) said it will establish
a new joint venture gold mine in the Northern Territory at a cost of
about 21 mln dlrs.  The mine, to be known as the Goodall project, will
be owned 60 pct by WMC and 40 pct by a local W.R. Grace and Co &lt;GRA&gt;
