SUBROTO SAYS INDONESIA SUPPORTS TIN PACT EXTENSION

JAKARTA, April 8 -

Mines and Energy Minister Subroto confirmed Indonesian support for an
extension of the sixth International Tin Agreement (ITA), but said a
new pact was not necessary.  Asked by Reuters to clarify his statement
on Monday in which he said the pact should be allowed to lapse,
Subroto said Indonesia was ready to back extension of the ITA.  "We
can support extension of the sixth agreement," he said. "But a seventh
accord we believe to be unnecessary."  The sixth ITA will expire at
the end of June unless a two-thirds majority of members vote for an
extension.  REUTER


